[There have been numerous JE cases in north eastern India again in 2015, along with some cases of encephalopathy and hypoglycemia associated with consumption of lychee fruit containing phytotoxins, specifically alpha-(methylenecyclopropyl)glycine. Although lychee consumption is not mentioned as a possible cause of acute encephalitis syndrome, Meghalaya and Assam states are within the lychee-producing areas in northern India http://www.mapsofindia.com/indiaagriculture/fruits-map/litchi-producing-states.html.

Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/images2/india-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3581103,306, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3581103,319. - Mod.TY]
